If I emerge alive from the pandemic — with asthma, I’m not confident — I plan to spend less and rely on myself more.
If people like me cut back, will that prevent the economy from recovering, and take a lot of jobs with it?
I loved jumping from rock to rock in the stream, and looking at the tadpoles.
Urban planners and futurists predicted that people would move away from cities, because they could work anywhere.
But now that we know that life at home works, will young people give up their shabby, crowded apartments?